    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 is a superlative example of the E46 chassis, powered by the S54B32 3.2L inline-six featuring individual throttle bodies and a high-pressure Double VANOS system recently calibrated to factory specifications. The powertrain is mated to a crisp Getrag 420G 6-speed manual transmission, delivering torque through an M-Variable Differential Lock. This specimen features a structurally sound floor pan with preventative subframe reinforcement already performed. The suspension maintains its factory-correct kinematics, and the rod bearings have been addressed as a proactive measure. Finished in original paint with no discernible orange peel or clear coat failure, and an interior free of bolster wear or pixel degradation, this is a mechanically flawless, collector-grade driver's car.",
